Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. PSI reviewed by the parties. State placed negotiations on the record. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 24 YEARS, with credit for 310 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 14 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 10 YEARS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program. The defendant is not appropriate for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court costs, fees, and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
1) Participate in educational training or vocational training;
2) Maintain full-time employment of at least 30 hours per week. If not employed full time, participate in vocational training;
3) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
4) Court set restitution at ZERO;
5) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
6) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal substances;
7) Defendant may not be present where drugs are consumed, packaged for sale, or sold;
8) No possession of drug paraphernalia;
9) Random urine screens;
10) AODA assessment and comply with recommended treatment;
11) Participate in a cognitive thinking class;
12) Comply with all rules as set forth by agent;
13) No contact with the victims family including Donna G.;

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting 

